verses.text_plain: And after the uproar was ceased, Paul called unto him the disciples, and embraced them, and departed for to go into Macedonia.
verses.verse_html: 1And after the uproar was ceased, Paul called unto him the disciples, and embraced them, and departed for to go into Macedonia.

verses.text_plain: And when he had gone over those parts, and had given them much exhortation, he came into Greece,
verses.verse_html: 2And when he had gone over those parts, and had given them much exhortation, he came into Greece,

verses.text_plain: And there abode three months. And when the Jews laid wait for him, as he was about to sail into Syria, he purposed to return through Macedonia.
verses.verse_html: 3And there abode three months. And when the Jews laid wait for him, as he was about to sail into Syria, he purposed to return through Macedonia.

verses.text_plain: And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus.
verses.verse_html: 4And there accompanied him into Asia Sopater of Berea; and of the Thessalonians, Aristarchus and Secundus; and Gaius of Derbe, and Timotheus; and of Asia, Tychicus and Trophimus.

verses.text_plain: These going before tarried for us at Troas.
verses.verse_html: 5These going before tarried for us at Troas.

verses.text_plain: And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread, and came unto them to Troas in five days; where we abode seven days.
verses.verse_html: 6And we sailed away from Philippi after the days of unleavened bread, and came unto them to Troas in five days; where we abode seven days.

verses.text_plain: And upon the first day of the week, when the disciples came together to break bread, Paul preached unto them, ready to depart on the morrow; and continued his speech until midnight.
verses.verse_html: 7And upon the first day of the week, when the disciples came together to break bread, Paul preached unto them, ready to depart on the morrow; and continued his speech until midnight.

verses.text_plain: And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.
verses.verse_html: 8And there were many lights in the upper chamber, where they were gathered together.

verses.text_plain: And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead.
verses.verse_html: 9And there sat in a window a certain young man named Eutychus, being fallen into a deep sleep: and as Paul was long preaching, he sunk down with sleep, and fell down from the third loft, and was taken up dead.

verses.text_plain: And Paul went down, and fell on him, and embracing him said, Trouble not yourselves; for his life is in him.
verses.verse_html: 10And Paul went down, and fell on him, and embracing him said, Trouble not yourselves; for his life is in him.

verses.text_plain: When he therefore was come up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, and talked a long while, even till break of day, so he departed.
verses.verse_html: 11When he therefore was come up again, and had broken bread, and eaten, and talked a long while, even till break of day, so he departed.

tokens.text: he therefore was come up again

verses.text_plain: And they brought the young man alive, and were not a little comforted.
verses.verse_html: 12And they brought the young man alive, and were not a little comforted.

verses.text_plain: And we went before to ship, and sailed unto Assos, there intending to take in Paul: for so had he appointed, minding himself to go afoot.
verses.verse_html: 13And we went before to ship, and sailed unto Assos, there intending to take in Paul: for so had he appointed, minding himself to go afoot.

verses.text_plain: And when he met with us at Assos, we took him in, and came to Mitylene.
verses.verse_html: 14And when he met with us at Assos, we took him in, and came to Mitylene.

verses.text_plain: And we sailed thence, and came the next day over against Chios; and the next day we arrived at Samos, and tarried at Trogyllium; and the next day we came to Miletus.
verses.verse_html: 15And we sailed thence, and came the next day over against Chios; and the next day we arrived at Samos, and tarried at Trogyllium; and the next day we came to Miletus.

verses.text_plain: For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.
verses.verse_html: 16For Paul had determined to sail by Ephesus, because he would not spend the time in Asia: for he hasted, if it were possible for him, to be at Jerusalem the day of Pentecost.

verses.text_plain: And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called the elders of the church.
verses.verse_html: 17And from Miletus he sent to Ephesus, and called the elders of the church.

verses.text_plain: And when they were come to him, he said unto them, Ye know, from the first day that I came into Asia, after what manner I have been with you at all seasons,
verses.verse_html: 18And when they were come to him, he said unto them, Ye know, from the first day that I came into Asia, after what manner I have been with you at all seasons,

verses.text_plain: Serving the Lord with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and temptations, which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews:
verses.verse_html: 19Serving the Lord with all humility of mind, and with many tears, and temptations, which befell me by the lying in wait of the Jews:

verses.text_plain: And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have shewed you, and have taught you publickly, and from house to house,
verses.verse_html: 20And how I kept back nothing that was profitable unto you, but have shewed you, and have taught you publickly, and from house to house,

verses.text_plain: Testifying both to the Jews, and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ.
verses.verse_html: 21Testifying both to the Jews, and also to the Greeks, repentance toward God, and faith toward our Lord Jesus Christ.

verses.text_plain: And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:
verses.verse_html: 22And now, behold, I go bound in the spirit unto Jerusalem, not knowing the things that shall befall me there:

verses.text_plain: Save that the Holy Ghost witnesseth in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions abide me.
verses.verse_html: 23Save that the Holy Ghost witnesseth in every city, saying that bonds and afflictions abide me.

verses.text_plain: But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.
verses.verse_html: 24But none of these things move me, neither count I my life dear unto myself, so that I might finish my course with joy, and the ministry, which I have received of the Lord Jesus, to testify the gospel of the grace of God.

verses.text_plain: And now, behold, I know that ye all, among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.
verses.verse_html: 25And now, behold, I know that ye all, among whom I have gone preaching the kingdom of God, shall see my face no more.

verses.text_plain: Wherefore I take you to record this day, that I am pure from the blood of all men.
verses.verse_html: 26Wherefore I take you to record this day, that I am pure from the blood of all men.

verses.text_plain: For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.
verses.verse_html: 27For I have not shunned to declare unto you all the counsel of God.

verses.text_plain: Take heed therefore unto yourselves, and to all the flock, over the which the Holy Ghost hath made you overseers, to feed the church of God, which he hath purchased with his own blood.
verses.verse_html: 28Take heed therefore unto yourselves, and to all the flock, over the which the Holy Ghost hath made you overseers, to feed the church of God, which he hath purchased with his own blood.

verses.text_plain: For I know this, that after my departing shall grievous wolves enter in among you, not sparing the flock.
verses.verse_html: 29For I know this, that after my departing shall grievous wolves enter in among you, not sparing the flock.

verses.text_plain: Also of your own selves shall men arise, speaking perverse things, to draw away disciples after them.
verses.verse_html: 30Also of your own selves shall men arise, speaking perverse things, to draw away disciples after them.

verses.text_plain: Therefore watch, and remember, that by the space of three years I ceased not to warn every one night and day with tears.
verses.verse_html: 31Therefore watch, and remember, that by the space of three years I ceased not to warn every one night and day with tears.

tokens.text: by the space of three years

verses.text_plain: And now, brethren, I commend you to God, and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance among all them which are sanctified.
verses.verse_html: 32And now, brethren, I commend you to God, and to the word of his grace, which is able to build you up, and to give you an inheritance among all them which are sanctified.

verses.text_plain: I have coveted no man’s silver, or gold, or apparel.
verses.verse_html: 33I have coveted no man’s silver, or gold, or apparel.

verses.text_plain: Yea, ye yourselves know, that these hands have ministered unto my necessities, and to them that were with me.
verses.verse_html: 34Yea, ye yourselves know, that these hands have ministered unto my necessities, and to them that were with me.

verses.text_plain: I have shewed you all things, how that so labouring ye ought to support the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he said, It is more blessed to give than to receive.
verses.verse_html: 35I have shewed you all things, how that so labouring ye ought to support the weak, and to remember the words of the Lord Jesus, how he said, It is more blessed to give than to receive.

verses.text_plain: And when he had thus spoken, he kneeled down, and prayed with them all.
verses.verse_html: 36And when he had thus spoken, he kneeled down, and prayed with them all.

verses.text_plain: And they all wept sore, and fell on Paul’s neck, and kissed him,
verses.verse_html: 37And they all wept sore, and fell on Paul’s neck, and kissed him,

verses.text_plain: Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spake, that they should see his face no more. And they accompanied him unto the ship.
verses.verse_html: 38Sorrowing most of all for the words which he spake, that they should see his face no more. And they accompanied him unto the ship.
